com.intuit.wasabi.api

Class LogsResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intuit.wasabi.api.LogsResource

  • public class LogsResource
extends Object
    The API endpoint /logs provides audit logs for application admins. The logs can be filtered, sorted, paginated. By default the page APISwaggerResource.DEFAULT_PAGE is returned, containing the last APISwaggerResource.DEFAULT_PER_PAGE actions. The logs are by default sorted by their occurence date, descending.

        • filtered,

        • counted,

        For details on how the filtering and sorting work, especially for the grammar structures used, see AuditLog.filter(List, String) and AuditLog.sort(List, String).
        Parameters:
        authorizationHeader - the authentication headers
        applicationName - the name of the application for which the log should be fetched

        filter - the filter rules
        timezoneOffset - the timezone offset from GMT
        Returns:
        a response containing a list with 0 - perPage experiments, if that many are on the page.
